When you put #custom-network in that big list at the top with color: #ffffff, GTK applies that white color to the label. Because CSS "inheritance" in GTK is aggressive, a simple #custom-network { color: #ebdbb2; } later in the file often fails to override the label's inherited white. By targeting #custom-network label, you are being more specific than the bulk rule.

One final "Gotcha"
Since your script outputs JSON, check if it includes a "class" attribute. If your script outputs {"text": "...", "class": "wifi"}, the ID becomes #custom-network.wifi. If your CSS only says #custom-network, it might ignore it.

